===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|scharp}}, from {{inh|en|ang|sċearp}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*skarpaz}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*(s)kerb-}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|skerp}}, {{cog|nds|scharp}}, {{cog|nl|scherp}}, {{cog|de|scharf}}, {{cog|da|skarp}}. Compare Irish {{m|ga|cearb|t=keen; cutting}}, Latin {{m|la|acerbus|t=tart, bitter}}, Tocharian B {{m|xtb|kärpye|t=rough}}, Latvian {{m|lt|skârbs|t=sharp, rough}}, Russian {{m|ru|щерба|t=notch}}, Albanian {{m|sq|harb|t=rudeness}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*(s)ker-|t=to cut}}. More at {{l|en|shear}}.

